{
  "info": {
    "name": "FreelanceFlow API",
    "description": "FreelanceFlow — NestJS backend for French-market freelance invoicing.\n\n**Base URL:** `{{baseUrl}}`  (default: http://localhost:3001/api/v1)\n\n**Full run order:**\n1. Health (optional)\n2. Auth Setup (Register → Login)\n3. Users (profile + optional logo)\n3a. Dashboard summary (optional)\n4. Clients (create only — delete is in Cleanup)\n5. Services (create only — delete is in Cleanup)\n6. Invoices (draft → sent → optional CSV export / queue email)\n7. PDF (download while invoice is 'sent')\n8. Invoices — Teardown (cancel → delete)\n9. Cleanup (delete service → delete client)\n10. Auth Teardown (refresh → logout)\n\n**Notes:** `GET /health` returns Terminus JSON (`database`, optional `redis` if `REDIS_URL` is set) plus `gitSha` and `env`. **Send invoice email** returns **202** with `jobId` when SMTP + queue are configured; otherwise **503**. **Exports CSV** — use **Send and Download** in Postman.\n\n**Why this order?** Deleting a client or service requires no linked invoice to exist (FK constraint). The invoice must be deleted first, which requires it to be in draft or cancelled state.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:3001/api/v1", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "clientId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "serviceId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "invoiceId", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1 — Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Liveness check",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["health"] },
            "description": "Terminus health: `database` (PostgreSQL), `redis` (only checked when `REDIS_URL` is set). Top-level `gitSha`, `env`. **503** if DB down or Redis required but unreachable."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2 — Auth Setup",
      "description": "Register (409 on re-run is expected) then Login. Login always sets the token.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (json.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', json.access_token);",
                  "    console.log('accessToken saved from register');",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"sophie@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"securePassword123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "register"]
            },
            "description": "201 on first run, 409 Conflict on re-runs (user already exists — Login below still sets the token)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (json.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', json.access_token);",
                  "    console.log('accessToken saved from login');",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"sophie@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"securePassword123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3 — Users",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get profile",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/users/profile",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["users", "profile"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update profile",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"displayName\": \"Sophie Martin\",\n  \"legalName\": \"Sophie Marie Martin\",\n  \"companyName\": \"SophieDev SARL\",\n  \"addressLine1\": \"123 rue de la Paix\",\n  \"addressLine2\": \"Appartement 4B\",\n  \"postalCode\": \"75001\",\n  \"city\": \"Paris\",\n  \"country\": \"FR\",\n  \"vatNumber\": \"FR12345678901\",\n  \"siret\": \"12345678901234\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/users/profile",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["users", "profile"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Upload profile logo (multipart)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "logo",
                  "description": "PNG, JPEG ou WebP — voir contraintes taille/dimensions dans Swagger.",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": []
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/users/profile/logo",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["users", "profile", "logo"]
            },
            "description": "**201** avec `logoStorageKey`. Remplace un logo existant. Champ formulaire attendu : **logo**."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get profile logo (image)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/users/profile/logo",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["users", "profile", "logo"]
            },
            "description": "Flux image (`image/png`, `jpeg`, ou `webp`). **404** si aucun logo."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3a — Dashboard",
      "description": "Résumé CA TTC (factures payées) et comptages par statut.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Dashboard summary",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/dashboard/summary",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["dashboard", "summary"]
            },
            "description": "JSON : CA TTC, volumes par statut de facture (EUR)."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "4 — Clients",
      "description": "Delete is in section 8 — Cleanup (must happen after invoice is deleted).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create client",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('clientId', json.id);",
                  "  console.log('clientId saved:', json.id);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Sophie Martin\",\n  \"email\": \"sophie@acme.fr\",\n  \"company\": \"Acme SAS\",\n  \"addressLine1\": \"42 rue du Commerce\",\n  \"zipCode\": \"75015\",\n  \"city\": \"Paris\",\n  \"country\": \"FR\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/clients", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["clients"] },
            "description": "Champs adresse alignés sur `CreateClientDto` : `addressLine1`, `zipCode`, `city` (obligatoires) ; `country` optionnel (défaut côté persistance souvent FR)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List clients",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/clients", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["clients"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get client",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/clients/{{clientId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["clients", "{{clientId}}"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update client",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Sophie Martin (updated)\",\n  \"email\": \"sophie.updated@acme.fr\",\n  \"company\": \"Acme SAS\",\n  \"addressLine1\": \"10 avenue Victor Hugo\",\n  \"zipCode\": \"75016\",\n  \"city\": \"Paris\",\n  \"country\": \"FR\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/clients/{{clientId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["clients", "{{clientId}}"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Export clients (CSV)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/clients/export",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["clients", "export"]
            },
            "description": "`text/csv; charset=utf-8` avec BOM UTF-8. **Send and Download** dans Postman."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "5 — Services (Prestations)",
      "description": "Delete is in section 8 — Cleanup (must happen after invoice is deleted).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create service",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('serviceId', json.id);",
                  "  console.log('serviceId saved:', json.id);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"title\": \"Développement backend\",\n  \"hourlyRateHt\": 150.00\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/services", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["services"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List services",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/services", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["services"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get service",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/services/{{serviceId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["services", "{{serviceId}}"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update service",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"title\": \"Développement backend senior\",\n  \"hourlyRateHt\": 175.00\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/services/{{serviceId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["services", "{{serviceId}}"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "6 — Invoices",
      "description": "Create and manage invoice through draft → sent state. PDF download follows in section 7.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create invoice",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('invoiceId', json.id);",
                  "  console.log('invoiceId saved:', json.id);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"clientId\": \"{{clientId}}\",\n  \"issueDate\": \"2026-04-11\",\n  \"dueDate\": \"2026-05-11\",\n  \"currency\": \"EUR\",\n  \"lines\": [\n    {\n      \"lineOrder\": 1,\n      \"description\": \"Développement backend — sprint 1\",\n      \"quantity\": 10,\n      \"unitPriceHt\": 150.00,\n      \"vatRate\": 0.20\n    },\n    {\n      \"serviceId\": \"{{serviceId}}\",\n      \"lineOrder\": 2,\n      \"description\": \"Conseil architecture\",\n      \"quantity\": 2,\n      \"unitPriceHt\": 150.00,\n      \"vatRate\": 0.20\n    }\n  ]\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/invoices", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["invoices"] },
            "description": "Line 2 links `serviceId` — unit price is snapshotted from the service's current rate."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List invoices",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/invoices", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["invoices"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get invoice",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/invoices/{{invoiceId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["invoices", "{{invoiceId}}"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update invoice metadata (draft only)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"issueDate\": \"2026-04-12\",\n  \"dueDate\": \"2026-05-12\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/invoices/{{invoiceId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["invoices", "{{invoiceId}}"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Replace invoice lines (draft only)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"lines\": [\n    {\n      \"lineOrder\": 1,\n      \"description\": \"Développement backend — sprint 2 (updated)\",\n      \"quantity\": 15,\n      \"unitPriceHt\": 150.00,\n      \"vatRate\": 0.20\n    }\n  ]\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/invoices/{{invoiceId}}/lines",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["invoices", "{{invoiceId}}", "lines"]
            },
            "description": "Replaces ALL lines atomically. Totals are recalculated."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Send invoice (draft → sent)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"status\": \"sent\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/invoices/{{invoiceId}}/status",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["invoices", "{{invoiceId}}", "status"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Mark invoice as paid (sent → paid)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"status\": \"paid\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/invoices/{{invoiceId}}/status",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["invoices", "{{invoiceId}}", "status"]
            },
            "description": "Transition **sent → paid** (renseigne `paidAt`). Utile pour le **Dashboard** (CA TTC des payées). **Attention :** une facture `paid` n’a **aucune** transition suivante — ne l’exécutez pas si vous comptez enchaîner avec la section **8 — Teardown** (annulation) sur la même facture."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Export invoices (CSV)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/invoices/export",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["invoices", "export"]
            },
            "description": "`text/csv; charset=utf-8` avec BOM UTF-8. **Send and Download** dans Postman."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Queue send invoice email (202)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"to\": [\"sophie@acme.fr\"],\n  \"subject\": \"Facture FreelanceFlow\",\n  \"body\": \"Bonjour,\\n\\nVeuillez trouver ci-joint notre facture en PDF.\\n\\nCordialement,\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/invoices/{{invoiceId}}/send-email",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["invoices", "{{invoiceId}}", "send-email"]
            },
            "description": "**202 Accepted** avec `jobId` si SMTP + file (Redis/Bull) sont configurés. **503** si email ou file indisponible. **400** si facture annulée. Limite **429** possible (throttle). Ne confirme pas la livraison chez le destinataire."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "7 — PDF",
      "description": "Invoice is in 'sent' state at this point — PDF generation works on any status.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Download invoice PDF",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/pdf/invoices/{{invoiceId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["pdf", "invoices", "{{invoiceId}}"]
            },
            "description": "Returns `application/pdf`. In Postman click **Send and Download** to save the file."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "8 — Invoices Teardown",
      "description": "Annuler (`sent` → `cancelled`) puis supprimer la facture. **Impossible** si la facture est passée en **`paid`** (aucune transition depuis `paid`) — dans ce cas créez une autre facture de test ou n’exécutez pas « Mark as paid » avant le teardown.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Cancel invoice (sent → cancelled)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"status\": \"cancelled\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/invoices/{{invoiceId}}/status",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["invoices", "{{invoiceId}}", "status"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete invoice (cancelled → 204)",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/invoices/{{invoiceId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["invoices", "{{invoiceId}}"]
            },
            "description": "Only draft or cancelled invoices can be deleted."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "9 — Cleanup",
      "description": "Safe to delete now that no invoice references these resources.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Delete service",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/services/{{serviceId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["services", "{{serviceId}}"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete client",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/clients/{{clientId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["clients", "{{clientId}}"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "10 — Auth Teardown",
      "description": "Refresh and Logout run last so the token stays valid throughout the run.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Refresh token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (json.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', json.access_token);",
                  "    console.log('accessToken rotated from refresh');",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "refresh"]
            },
            "description": "Uses the HttpOnly `refreshToken` cookie set by Login. Postman sends cookies automatically."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', '');",
                  "  console.log('accessToken cleared — session ended');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/logout",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "logout"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
